SQL Queries and Results on Customers Dataset
1. Select the first 5 rows from the table
SQL: SELECT * FROM customers LIMIT 5; Answer:
customerid gender age paymentmethod
C241288 Female 28.0 Credit Card
C111565 Male 21.0 Debit Card
C266599 Male 20.0 Cash
C988172 Female 66.0 Credit Card
C189076 Female 53.0 Cash
2. Total number of customers
SQL: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM customers; Answer: 99,457
3. Unique payment methods
SQL:SELECTDISTINCTpaymentmethodFROMcustomers; Answer:CreditCard,DebitCard,Cash
4. Number of customers by gender
SQL: SELECT gender, COUNT(*) FROM customers GROUP BY gender; Answer:
Female: 59,482, Male: 39,975
5. Average age of all customers
SQL: SELECT AVG(age) FROM customers; Answer: 43.43 years
6. Customer IDs and ages of the 5 oldest customers
SQL:SELECTcustomerid,ageFROMcustomersORDERBYageDESCLIMIT5
7. Number of customers older than 50
SQL: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM customers WHERE age ¿ 50; Answer: 36,054
8. Customers using Credit Card
SQL:SELECTCOUNT(*)FROMcustomersWHEREpaymentmethod =′ CreditCard′; Answer:34,931
9. Minimum and maximum age
SQL: SELECTMIN(age), MAX(age) FROM customers; Answer: Min: 18.0, Max: 69.0
10. Count customers by payment method in descend
ing order
SQL:SELECTpaymentmethod,COUNT(∗)ascountFROMcustomersGROUPBYpaymentmethodORDERBYcountDESC
44, 447,CreditCard : 34,931,DebitCard : 20,079
11. Average age by gender
SQL: SELECT gender, AVG(age) FROM customers GROUP BY gender; 
male: 43.45, Male: 43.38
12. Customers exactly 30 years old
SQL: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM customers WHERE age = 30; Answer: 1,978
13. Customers aged between 20 and 25
SQL: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM customers WHERE age BETWEEN 20 AND 25;
Answer: 11,570
14. First 5 customer IDs using Debit Card
SQL:SELECTcustomeridFROMcustomersWHEREpaymentmethod =′ DebitCard′LIMIT5; 
15. Most frequent payment method for customers
over 60
SQL:SELECTpaymentmethod,COUNT(∗)FROMcustomersWHEREage > 60GROUPBYpayment
16. Customers whose ID starts with ’C1’
SQL:SELECTCOUNT(*)FROMcustomersWHEREcustomeridLIKE′C1Answer:31,259
17. Average age of customers using Cash
SQL:SELECTAVG(age)FROMcustomersWHEREpaymentmethod =′ Cash′; Answer:43.45years
18. Count of customers NOT using Cash
SQL:SELECTCOUNT(*)FROMcustomersWHEREpaymentmethod! =′ Cash′; Answer:55,010
19. Gender distribution of customers using DebitCard
SQL:SELECTgender, COUNT(*)FROMcustomersWHEREpaymentmethod =′ DebitCard′GROUPBYgender;
20. Customers with null age
SQL: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM customers WHERE age IS NULL; Answer: 119
